OL,3,C'Devious' woman stabbed husband in the
OL,4,Cback after row, court told
OL,6,F"But generally each party learns to
OL,7,Flive with the other, or else leaves."
OL,9,FJurors were told that Mrs Rawle had
OL,10,Fattacked her husband twice before,
OL,11,Fonce with a fork and once with a knife.
OL,13,FMr Brunton added: "Once she put a
OL,14,Fhosepipe through the window of her
OL,15,Fhusband's car and filled it with
OL,16,Fwater. They would slap each other,
OL,17,Fpush each other, call each other nasty
OL,18,Fnames."
